<html>
    <head>
        <title>Something went wrong :-(</title>
        <style>
            body {
                font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;
                width: 500px;
                margin-left: auto;
                margin-right: auto;
                margin-top: 20px;
            }

            h1 {
                font-family: Trebuchet MS, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;
            }

            @media only screen and (min-width: 960px) {
                .content {
                    margin-left: 200px;
                    margin-right: 200px;
                }
            }

            .our-twitter-feed {
                width: 25em;
            }

            .footer {
                font-size: smaller;
                color: #888888;
                text-align: center;
            }
        </style>
    </head>

    <body>
        <img src="https://s3.amazonaws.com/pythonanywhere-error-images/logo-234x35.png" />

        <div class="main">
            <h1>Something went wrong :-(</h1>

            <p>
                PythonAnywhere is having some issues. Our ever-vigilant sysadmins have been notified and are on the case.
            </p>
            <p>
                Please try again in a little while.
            </p>
            <p>
                For possible status updates, keep an eye on our Twitter feed:
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="our-twitter-feed">
            <a
                class="twitter-timeline"
                href="https://twitter.com/pythonanywhere?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">
                Tweets by pythonanywhere
            </a>
            <script async src="https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" charset="utf-8"></script>
        </div>

        <footer class="footer">
            <p>Copyright &copy;2011-2021 PythonAnywhere LLP</p>
        </footer>
    </body>
</html>
